---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';

const title = `Terms of Use | ${SITE.name}`;
const description =
  'Terms of Use for Payoff Logic: educational purpose of our calculators, accuracy disclaimer, limitation of liability, and acceptable use.';
const lastUpdated = 'July 11, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12 sm:px-6">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-navy-900">Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-navy-500">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-navy-700">
      <p>
        By accessing or using {SITE.name} (the "Site"), you agree to these
        Terms of Use. If you do not agree, please do not use the Site.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">1. Educational purpose — not financial advice</h2>
      <p>
        All calculators, articles, and other content on the Site are provided
        for <strong>general educational and informational purposes only</strong>.
        Nothing on the Site constitutes financial, investment, legal, tax, or
        accounting advice, and nothing on the Site should be relied upon as a
        substitute for advice from a qualified professional who knows your
        individual circumstances. We are not a lender, broker, or registered
        financial advisor.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">2. Accuracy of results</h2>
      <p>
        Calculator results are estimates based solely on the values you enter
        and the stated assumptions of each tool. Actual loan terms, rates,
        taxes, insurance premiums, and fees vary by lender, location, credit
        profile, and market conditions, and may differ materially from any
        estimate shown here. While we test our calculators against verified
        reference examples, we do not guarantee that any result is
        error-free, complete, or suitable for your purpose.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">3. No warranty</h2>
      <p>
        The Site and all content are provided <strong>"as is" and "as
        available"</strong> without warranties of any kind, express or
        implied, including but not limited to warranties of merchantability,
        fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">4. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, {SITE.name} and its operators
        shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental,
        consequential, or special damages arising out of or in connection with
        your use of the Site or reliance on any content or calculator result,
        even if advised of the possibility of such damages. Your sole and
        exclusive remedy for dissatisfaction with the Site is to stop using it.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">5. Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>You agree not to:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li>Scrape, harvest, or republish Site content at scale without permission;</li>
        <li>Interfere with the Site's operation or attempt to gain unauthorized access;</li>
        <li>Use the Site in any way that violates applicable law.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">6. Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        The Site's design, text, and code are owned by {SITE.name} or its
        licensors and are protected by copyright. You may link to any page and
        print results for personal use. Any other reproduction requires prior
        written permission.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">7. Third-party links and advertising</h2>
      <p>
        The Site may contain links to third-party websites and may display
        third-party advertising. We do not control and are not responsible for
        the content, policies, or practices of third-party sites. A link or ad
        is not an endorsement.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">8. Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms at any time by posting a revised version on
        this page with an updated "last updated" date. Continued use of the
        Site after changes constitutes acceptance.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">9. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms? Reach us via the
        <a href="/contact/" class="text-navy-900 underline hover:text-navy-600">contact page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
